5000|$|On {{the other}} side, the Catechism of the Catholic Church states that an {{ordination}} ceremony performed {{on a woman}} would be invalid as well as illicit; this doctrine {{is found in the}} writings of Thomas Aquinas and many others. Pope <b>John</b> <b>Paul</b> <b>II</b> <b>has</b> written [...] "Priestly ordination, which hands on the office entrusted by Christ to his Apostles of teaching, sanctifying and governing the faithful, has in the Catholic Church from the beginning always been reserved to men alone" [...] in his Apostolic Letter, Ordinatio Sacerdotalis. This is reflected in the current Code of Canon Law.|$|E
